	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Necros Guide lvl 1-44</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:">Darkath</a> | 
		            3/1/2001 3:33:29 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">OK, here is some input for all you wanna-be necros to know what are you against. This is a deep recompilation of my necroing wisdom; I hope it serves you well. Since I don&#8217;t have the IKS stats ill leave them out of this Guide, anyway I never thought too well about IKS necros =). <BR>
<BR>
First off: RACE<BR>
<BR>
This small pros and cons race guide will be ordered from higher to lower base int.<BR>
<BR>
Erudite: <BR>
&#183;	Highest Base int + (117)<BR>
&#183;	Liked at home town (paineel) +<BR>
&#183;	Best area to gather bonechips on norrath +<BR>
&#183;	Bad agi which determines how often you are hit and when channeling works &#8211;<BR>
&#183;	Blind at night &#8211;<BR>
&#183;	Cant leave continent till lvl 8 (invis) &#8211;<BR>
<BR>
Darkelf: (my favorite)<BR>
&#183;	2nd Highest base int + (109)<BR>
&#183;	Liked at home town +<BR>
&#183;	Good surroundings / quests for fast lvling +<BR>
&#183;	Good Agi +<BR>
&#183;	Most hated of all Necro combinations (besides Iks necro) &#8211;<BR>
<BR>
Gnome: <BR>
&#183;	3rd Highest base int + (108)<BR>
&#183;	Good Agi +<BR>
&#183;	Not very Hated all around +<BR>
&#183;	Not liked at town &#8211;<BR>
&#183;	Not very good newbie area &#8211;<BR>
<BR>
Human:<BR>
&#183;	&#8230; hmm&#8230; Ill really leave this race out of the question, lets say nobody in his/her right mind would make a human Necro =)<BR>
<BR>
I picked a DE necro and I wouldn&#8217;t regret a single sec my choice. We got good night vision, no problems at town, good hunting areas and such. And since adding points to int over 200, those 8 points less that I had than an Erudite haven&#8217;t made a difference. By lvl 35 I already had 201 and much better all around stats. But its your choice, I just suggested mine. Another reason is that since you are really KOS on most places, you get much more variety as a DE to hunt NPC&#8217;s, Does it matter if you are more hated than KOS? I think not.<BR>
<BR>
STATS:<BR>
<BR>
Stats are an important issue on every EQ character&#8217;s life. Necros as all other pure casters use INT or intelligence. The higher to lower in as shown above is Erud, DE, Gnome, Hum/Iks. Eruds have 8 more points that DE&#8217;s but since having 134 or 142 of int (after adding the starting points you are give) isn&#8217;t a really big difference out of 200 and having both agi/dex on 60 (erud case) or having both on 90 (DE case) IS a difference Id choose a DE.<BR>
<BR>
IF you choose put as many points as possible on INT and the rest on agi. Here is what do Stats do:<BR>
<BR>
STR: How much you an carry since your not going to melee a lot<BR>
STA: How many HP you have, but your not to get hit so np<BR>
AGI: How often your Channeling skill works and how often you are missed by mobs<BR>
DEX: How often your dodge or similar skills raise their lvl<BR>
INT: How much mana you got<BR>
WIS: How often your trade skills success<BR>
CHA: How much merchants sell or buy stuff from you (minimal difference)<BR>
<BR>
WHERE and WHAT to HUNT: (if you chose a DE, this guide might be useful for other races but I do not respond for faction problems or other issues following this guide may cause)<BR>
<BR>
Lvl 1-2: Newbie log in Nektulous forest.<BR>
Lvl 3: Nro near the zone line to E. Freeport.<BR>
Lvl 4-5: Puntar Fisherman in the fishers village on Nro near the docks to Velious.<BR>
Lvl 6-7: The obelisk on Nek forest near the EC zone, prolly need someone to break it.<BR>
Lvl 8-11: Orcs in EC, took me 1 day to get from 8 to 12 doing this.<BR>
Lvl 12-15: Sisters or Errolisi on OOT.<BR>
Lvl 16: Crocs on oasis.<BR>
Lvl 17-21: Aviak Guards on Lake Rathe, bind at arena when hunting here.<BR>
Lvl 22-24: Treant on SK.<BR>
Lvl 25-28: Guards Tolus or Reskin on EC.<BR>
Lvl 29-30: Skulking brutes in the caves near Dalnir on Warslik woods.<BR>
Lvl 31-33: Overthere, grouping on FM ledge.<BR>
Lvl 34: Dorfs in BB, might be tough but nice xp.<BR>
Lvl 35: Go to Eastern Wastes on Velious, get in a group if not Solo orcs from fort.<BR>
Lvl 36-38: Guards Colin and Valon at WC.<BR>
Lvl 39-44: Druid ring on WC or Druid Obelisk on EC, solo.<BR>
<BR>
This is what I did and no way the only or the best hunting areas/spots. Some say there are better but with this I lvled really fast.<BR>
<BR>
LVLING INFO: (read this, important!)<BR>
<BR>
Lvl 4-5: With Puntar use darkness/fear and DOT him to hell. Then you should do dmg yourself with your dagger/staff and send pet ASAP if darkness doesn&#8217;t stick, if it does sent him after fearing Puntar.<BR>
<BR>
Lvl 8-11: Any orc belts your group gets try and get them with the &#8220;I&#8217;m trying to raise faction with Freeport&#8221; excuse, some ppl believe you and give you&#8217;re their belts, if they do or any belts you get give them in at the Warriors guild on W. Freeport nearby the arena to the guild leader (cant remember name, his got an eye patch I think, on room with a couple of tables on highest floor)<BR>
<BR>
Lvl 12-15: Sisters of Errolisi, first phase in which you get rich. Bind at the Docks on EFP and take the beat to Butcherblocks, once you get to see the shore of the first island and you are not to far from it jump off the boat and swim to the shore, once there get a pet and pull a sister, DON&#8217;T USE FEAR, the island is filled of sisters and there are some really tough ones. Take 4 empty backpacks and when you are totally full of Purity Belts gate back to FP, once there sell the Belts for aprox 1.2pp a piece! Rinse and Repeat<BR>
<BR>
Lvl 22-24: Treants, second phase you get rich. When hunting these bind near their hunting place but not too close. These guys drop around 3-4pp and about 20gp per kill, also drop Staffs worth 14pp apiece, if you get this staffs sell them at the Centaur Village that&#8217;s nearby. When you are filled to the limit of gp&#8217;s, shout for a banker, there are usual ones in this zone give them a bit for the job and keep fighting, do this every time you are over looted with money, then at the end of the hunting day, get a sow and go to Oggok (ogre city) and bank there, then gate back to the treant hunting site, I got like 2kpp on this lvls, you can stay more but there is better xp elsewhere, and this is a fast lvling guide.<BR>
<BR>
Lvl 25-28: Guard Tolus is a piece of cake, you don&#8217;t even need a pet. It would rather steal xp from you instead of helping you. Use your darkness spell, 4 SOP&#8217;s and he starts running (when the SOP&#8217;s hit fully). Watch out for Sergeant Slate, a lvl 40+ guard that walks between tolus and reskin. Tolus is at INN 2 and Reskin at INN 1. Always be SOWed, get one when it starts wearing off at the Tunnel, there is like 99% chances there is a druid/shaman there. They sometimes drop FS weps worth a couple of pp, sell at tunnel. Slate has an enormous Aggro range, if you can see him don&#8217;t attack Tolus-Reskin, if he follows you, FD or Zone to WC.<BR>
<BR>
Lvl 31-33: Don&#8217;t try soloing stuff here even if its white, it will shred your pet if it tanks a couple of secs, if you have sow kite stuff with all dots on it, anyway you prolly cant fear or it will last too short to be useful. Use the same excuse as you did on Orc belts to get as many Sarnak War Braids as possible, give them 4 ata time to the Undead captain on the Outpost, it is the only way to raise the faction, after this phase I turned from Apprehensive to indifferent and you get a bit of xp.<BR>
<BR>
Lvl 35: you can easily Solo Giants/ Rygorr orcs / walruses with darkness/invoke fear and the rest of the dots/DDs. Get ASAP Torbas acid blast from Thurgain it&#8217;s a nice upgrade for SOP.<BR>
<BR>
Lvl 39+: This is the biggest richening phase in your life, Druids drop either 1 or 2 FS weps per kill and bows worth 2pps. From 1 kill you can get around 10-12pp easily. If your hunting on WC, sell the weps to the Druid merchant on the ring, if hunting on EC sell them to the merchants on the inn nearby, there is an erud one that should sell/buy stuff from ya. Shout for a banker when you are over looted and try been sowed when possible, not necessary.<BR>
<BR>
NECROING TACTIC:<BR>
<BR>
The most common tactic is to darkness/fear NPCs, tho in some places is not recommended due to the dangers that are around you, if you got small space to fight kite stuff run from one side to another with the pet/dots on the mob. When possible try NOT to use a pet, it only drains XP in some cases (when hunting guard tolus/reskin). Be smart, FD whenever you see stuff isn&#8217;t going well.<BR>
<BR>
SKILLS:<BR>
<BR>
There is some important stuff relating necros and skills we acquire. We use mostly Conjuration and Alteration as spells, so I would recommend specializing on Alteration. Now other skills that we don&#8217;t use very much but that we need are Abjuration and Evocation. <BR>
<BR>
Abjuration: Used primarily to FD, if you get it to 100 skill lvl FD will work perfectly, also used to heal pet and cast stuff like Spirit armor and such. Cast minor shielding over and over to raise this skill<BR>
<BR>
Evocation: Used primarily on Undead only DD spells. But on lvl 44+ we get a spell which ISNT undead only and that&#8217;s an awesome DD, Ignite Bones. The problem is that we Don&#8217;t use too much Evocation. To use well Ignite bones the required skill lvl is around 180 I think so get evoc to 180 and then use Ignite bones. From lvl 8 onwards (first Evoc spell you get: ward undead) try to max out every lvl or wait till later lvls when you can cast over and over the Ward undead spell. I did this and my skill is up to 80 atm. So I need to practice more. Since at lower lvl ward undead is a really expensive manawise spell, Id recommend to get to like 20 and start practicing over and over the spell.<BR>
<BR>
STUFF YOU SHOULD KNOW:<BR>
<BR>
1) On higher lvls (24+) your pet gets much more resistant and powerful. It can receive 3x as much punishment as the lvl 20 one. BUT they usually get destroyed cause the mobs they fight are really hard hitters from this lvl onwards so it&#8217;s a must to Darkness/Fear ASAP or have the attention of the mob on you rather than on your pet. It can tank well, but don&#8217;t go thinking it&#8217;ll tank the whole fight for you. Life isn&#8217;t that easy.<BR>
<BR>
2) Don&#8217;t waste money on your lvl 1 pet, it sucks and it will prolly need you to tank for him. If you DO buy him, don&#8217;t let him taunt cause it will get destroyed real quickly.<BR>
<BR>
3) If you pick a DE as a race use when possible the Faction &#8220;problem&#8221; we have to get more stuff to complete quests (first example lvl 8 with orc belts)<BR>
<BR>
4) Have a weapon on your primary hand until you start hunting treants, from this onwards don&#8217;t use a wep cause you do no dmg and put yourself in risk, which is bad. Besides your pet can take more dmg from lvl 24 onwards so you got time to dark/fear the mob or kite him around<BR>
<BR>
5) DON&#8217;T twink your necro, you don&#8217;t need it since we are the class that gets big bucks first besides evil magicians.<BR>
<BR>
6) 2 Lvl 34 necro can take the druid rings on WC/EC, simple someone pulls and the other takes the add then fight one each. Piece of cake =)<BR>
<BR>
7) If you goto Velious don&#8217;t cast COB nearby NPCs, they go from whatever they con you (amiable, dubious, etc&#8230;) to instant KOS. According to Verant is cause &#8220;nobody like skeletons&#8221; *sigh*<BR>
<BR>
CLOSEING:<BR>
<BR>
I really have enjoyed my necro and will prolly take him to lvl 50+. I know that lvl 49 necros can solo seafury Cyclopes and finish the fight with full hp/mana and pet 100%, id love to see another class say that =). If you get stuck on lvls 35, 40, 45, 50+ don&#8217;t get disappointed, it took me 1 day to get past 30 and 5 days to get past 35. It is planned to be that way, so just keep going, you&#8217;ll see how strong you get when you get to the next circle of spells. If you DO get stuck, don&#8217;t stress it. Group, have fun and relax. It will pass its just 14 out of 60 lvls so don&#8217;t worry.<BR>
<BR>
Darkath lvl 37 Necromancer<BR>
Rodcet Nife server<BR>
<BR>
PS: Say hi if you find me online =)<BR>
<BR>
LONG LIVE THE NECRO!!!!<BR>

			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
