				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				OK now that im lvl 45 I want to update a bit the guide.<BR>
<BR>
I stioped on druids from lvl 39+, this is right you kill them till they turm green (that is around lvl 42 or 43) if you think the xp sucks, which actually I did but I was stunned with the loot, you go and kill the Dorfs on BB docks.<BR>
<BR>
There are 8 spawns on BB docks. 2 dorfs in some huts near a wall, 1 dorf at the beggining of the docks to Antonica and Kunark, 1 dorf at the end of the same docks, a dorf outside of the northen wall (you must swimm to get to him) and an elf on a hut near the High Elf Merchant.<BR>
<BR>
Now, usualy the 2 dorfs in huts and the 2 dorfs at the end of the docks are camped by druids, this is because they dont give - faction with guards, only with dorf citizens. the rest gives faction hit with dorf citizens and guards. Since we are a necro we dont really care about the faction hits so I say kill em all. they spawn time is 20 mins. I could manage to kill the elf in hut, the 2 at teh begginging of the docks and the outside on in less than 20 mins. on lvl 44+<BR>
I could kill them all except the 2 ones in the huts cause they come together in less than 20 mins.<BR>
<BR>
now youll be fearkiteing in the docks. its rather easy since they are slow and dark makes them even slower. now the dorfs on the docks to Kunark have the nasty habit of (when feared) run behind the huts with 2 dorfs and behind a green caster with a pet on another house near there guards. what you do to neutralize this is to dark them and pull them past the middle dock to the north. when they are past the middle docks, their pathing changes, now they run to guards but they are just SO slow they never even get close. your DDs and your (always Augmented) pet can deal with them easily. if they get too close to guards and aggro them (this never happned to me) FD near the water and /q cause you cant errase the aggro off these guards. the simply log on back.<BR>
<BR>
no that is really good xp, tho at lvl 44+ you might want to go kill spirocs =)<BR>
<BR>
I am planing to kill spriocs untill lvl 49, then solo SFs. the spriocs are located on the island where you land when you take the raft from Oasis to Kunarl. first you see some palm trees, then you see the ogre camp, a mountain and past that there is an exact copy of the South Karana Aviak Tree. tho this aviaks have red feathers and white/blue/yellow wings and are much higher lvl. this xp rocks tho NEVER give your back to one of these, they backstab for 250+ dmg, once got a BS for 360 dmg.<BR>
<BR>
with the spirocs have up at all times Steelskin ( not diamond skin its too expensive to cast) Archsheilding and DMF. if posible offer DMF for SoW it helps a lot.<BR>
<BR>
park your pet near some trees and pull singles. most pulls come doubles but there are usualy single spawns near the base of the house.<BR>
<BR>
well ive been doing this for a while now. im really dedicated to get items atm. if your interested on haveing a list of my equip send me a request to ccasassus@hotmail.com and ill send you back an excel file with my stuff. im planning as I said to kill Spirocs till 49 then solo SFs at OOT. then on lvl 50, get a hammer that procs tele to OT off a quest on the outpost in OT, and go kill Ice Giants on Everfrost, near the zone to perma. this giants give AWESOME loot, if you thought druids was heaving you havent seen anything yet. maybe 2-3k DAILY if you camp seriously the IGs and dont get it stolen. now the use of the hammer is to find a low green and hit him with the hammer till the weapon procs and you are gated over to OT, bank and simply gate back to action. do this when you are really fll with coin cause you might get it stole while you bank and gate back (yeah this camp is 24/7 hehe)<BR>
<BR>
anyway thouse are my 2 cp, I hope it servers you well. try and get Jboots asap, the Ancient Cyclops on OT is soloable on 49+ whereas the one on Sro is on 44 prolly or even less. Jboots make you totaly undependant, no more beggin for so to make your life easier, im planing to get them really soon, asap I hit 49.<BR>
<BR>
LONG LIVE THE NECRO!!!<BR>
<BR>
Darkath lvl 45 Necromancer
